.TH WALLPAPERMGR "1" "February 2026" "wallpapermgr 202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
wallpapermgr \- WallPaper ManaGeR for installing and managing wallpaper collections
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wallpapermgr
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR] [\fI\,WALLPAPER\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wallpapermgr
is a wallpaper management system for installing, updating, and managing wallpaper collections from preconfigured GitHub repositories. It provides a unified interface for managing curated wallpaper collections across various categories and themes.
.PP
wallpapermgr supports installation from the wallpapermgr organization repositories on GitHub, search functionality for discovering available wallpaper collections, and proper wallpaper version tracking. The tool is designed for desktop users who want to maintain organized wallpaper collections across multiple systems.
.PP
All wallpaper collections are managed through Git repositories, making it easy to version control, update, and synchronize wallpaper installations across different machines.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B list
List all wallpaper collections currently available in the wallpapermgr repository catalog
.TP
.B search \fI\,<term>\/\fR
Search for available wallpaper collections matching the specified term. Useful for finding collections by category or theme.
.TP
.B available
Show all available wallpaper collections from the GitHub repository. With authentication token configured, fetches complete list from GitHub API. Without token, shows predefined list.
.TP
.B install \fI\,<wallpaper>\/\fR
Install a wallpaper collection from the preconfigured repository. Downloads wallpaper files and installs them to the appropriate system location.
.TP
.B update \fI\,[wallpaper]\/\fR
Update wallpaper collections. If no wallpaper collection is specified, updates all installed collections. If a specific collection is provided, updates only that collection.
.TP
.B remove \fI\,<wallpaper>\/\fR
Remove an installed wallpaper collection and its files from the system
.TP
.B download \fI\,<wallpaper>\/\fR
Download or clone a wallpaper collection repository without installing. Useful for examining collections or manual installation.
.TP
.B cron \fI\,[add|remove|run]\/\fR
Manage automatic wallpaper collection updates via cron job. Add schedules periodic updates, remove cancels scheduled updates, run executes update immediately.
.TP
.B version \fI\,<wallpaper>\/\fR
Display version information for an installed wallpaper collection
