.SH SETTING WALLPAPERS
Wallpapers can be set using various desktop environment tools:
.SS GNOME
.RS
gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.background picture-uri 'file:///path/to/wallpaper.jpg'
.br
gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.background picture-uri-dark 'file:///path/to/dark-wallpaper.jpg'
.RE
.SS KDE Plasma
.RS
Use System Settings → Appearance → Wallpaper
.br
Or right-click desktop → Configure Desktop and Wallpaper
.RE
.SS Xfce
.RS
xfconf-query -c xfce4-desktop -p /backdrop/screen0/monitor0/workspace0/last-image -s /path/to/wallpaper.jpg
.RE
.SS Nitrogen (Standalone)
.RS
nitrogen /path/to/wallpaper/directory
.br
# Select wallpaper and click Apply
.RE
.SS feh (Standalone)
.RS
feh --bg-scale /path/to/wallpaper.jpg
.br
feh --bg-fill /path/to/wallpaper.jpg
.br
feh --bg-center /path/to/wallpaper.jpg
.RE
.SS Variety (Wallpaper Changer)
.RS
variety -f /path/to/wallpaper.jpg
.br
# Or configure sources in Variety preferences
.RE
